**Definition**
CRUD in Node.js refers to performing Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations on a database (like MongoDB) using a Node.js server, typically through Express routes.

**Types**

* Create (POST)
* Read (GET)
* Update (PUT/PATCH)
* Delete (DELETE)

**Working**
Node.js receives HTTP requests from the client, processes them through Express routes, and communicates with the database (MongoDB) using a driver or Mongoose. Each route corresponds to one CRUD action.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
Client → Express Route → MongoDB → Response
        POST  /create
        GET   /users
        PUT   /update/:id
        DELETE /delete/:id
```

**Advantages**

* Easy to build REST APIs
* JSON → BSON compatibility with MongoDB
* Fast non-blocking operations
* Clean separation of logic

**Disadvantages**

* Requires proper error handling
* Asynchronous operations need Promises/async–await
* Schema-less nature may cause inconsistent data

**Examples (Using Express + MongoDB)**

**1. Create (POST)**

```js
app.post("/users", async (req, res) => {
  const user = await db.collection("users").insertOne(req.body);
  res.send(user);
});
```

**2. Read (GET)**

```js
app.get("/users", async (req, res) => {
  const users = await db.collection("users").find().toArray();
  res.send(users);
});
```

**3. Update (PUT)**

```js
app.put("/users/:id", async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id;
  const result = await db.collection("users").updateOne(
    { _id: ObjectId(id) },
    { $set: req.body }
  );
  res.send(result);
});
```

**4. Delete (DELETE)**

```js
app.delete("/users/:id", async (req, res) => {
  const id = req.params.id;
  const result = await db.collection("users").deleteOne({ _id: ObjectId(id) });
  res.send(result);
});
```

**Short code snippets**
Connection setup:

```js
const { MongoClient, ObjectId } = require("mongodb");
const client = await MongoClient.connect(url);
const db = client.db("testdb");
```

**Applications**

* User management systems
* Inventory apps
* Login modules
* Admin dashboards
* Any CRUD-based REST API
